&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you a Registered Nurse, Occupational Therapist or a Social Worker looking for twilight working hours?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our Southampton community service, The Lighthouse, are looking for a Band 6 Senior Practitioner.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Southern Health NHS Foundation Trust are running this service in partnership with Solent Mind. The service is currently run by clinical staff employed by SHFT and Peer Specialists employed by Solent Mind.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Lighthouse is a self-referral, drop in service for anyone who feels they are experiencing a mental health crisis. It can be easily accessible to our community and open to all. The clinical model focuses on supporting visitors to self-manage and work in partnership with the staff to create safety plans based on peer support and practical, recovery focused approaches to their mental health. The model challenges more traditional prescriptive approaches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Examples of similar drop in services are, The Retreat in Bournemouth, run by Dorset Healthcare Trust and The Leeds Survivor Led Crisis Service.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will have the unique and innovative opportunity to be involved in the development of crisis care for adult mental health service users in the City of Southampton. They will have a drive and enthusiasm for crisis care and a passion for service development.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As a Senior Practitioner in the team, you will be taking a lead role in the support and supervision of your colleagues, as well as taking a positive role in the evaluation and continued development of the service. You will champion the clinical model and promote co-production at all levels of service development.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A comprehensive training and development package will be provided in trauma informed care and survivor led approaches to crisis care. You will participate in group supervision and reflective practice.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful applicants will be expected to participate in a flexible weekly rota working twilight shifts of 4pm - midnight. This post is for 37.5 hours per week.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you are interested in this vacancy, however you have any questions or would like to discuss further then we would be happy to hear from you, please feel free to get in touch with the Crisis Pathway Manager - Claire Ruiz on 02380 835535&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Happy to Talk Flexible Working- all requests for flexible and part time working will be considered.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
